# AI Negotiation Copilot - Coding Agent Rules

## Environment Rules
- ALWAYS use PowerShell commands (NOT bash/sh)
- ALWAYS use Windows path separators when needed
- ALWAYS activate Python venv with: .\venv\Scripts\activate
- NEVER use WSL or Linux-specific commands
- ALWAYS test commands work on native Windows 11

## Python Development Rules
- ALWAYS use Python 3.11+ features
- ALWAYS use async/await for I/O operations
- ALWAYS use type hints (from typing import ...)
- ALWAYS use Pydantic for data validation
- NEVER use blocking I/O in async functions
- ALWAYS handle exceptions gracefully
- ALWAYS log errors with proper context

## FastAPI Rules
- ALWAYS use FastAPI's dependency injection
- ALWAYS validate request/response with Pydantic models
- ALWAYS use APIRouter for endpoint organization
- ALWAYS implement proper error handlers
- NEVER expose internal errors to clients
- ALWAYS use async def for route handlers
- ALWAYS add OpenAPI documentation strings

## WebSocket Rules
- ALWAYS handle WebSocketDisconnect gracefully
- ALWAYS implement reconnection logic on client
- ALWAYS validate message schemas before processing
- NEVER block the WebSocket event loop
- ALWAYS use asyncio for concurrent operations
- ALWAYS implement heartbeat/ping-pong
- ALWAYS clean up resources on disconnect

## Gemini API Rules
- NEVER mock the Gemini API - use official SDK
- ALWAYS use google-genai (pip install google-genai) — NOT google-generativeai, NOT google-cloud-aiplatform
- ALWAYS import as: from google import genai / from google.genai import types
- ALWAYS use async with client.aio.live.connect(...) as session — NEVER call __aenter__() manually
- ALWAYS use GEMINI_MODEL_PRIMARY = "gemini-2.5-flash-native-audio-preview-12-2025"
- ALWAYS use GEMINI_MODEL_FALLBACK = "gemini-2.0-flash-live-preview-04-09" (gemini-2.0-flash-live-001 is DEAD since Dec 9 2025)
- NEVER use gemini-1.5-flash or gemini-1.5-flash-002 — they do NOT support the Live API
- ALWAYS handle API rate limits with exponential backoff
- ALWAYS stream responses when possible
- NEVER send PII without user consent
- ALWAYS validate API responses before using
- ALWAYS implement timeout handling

## Frontend Rules
- ALWAYS use TypeScript (no JavaScript)
- ALWAYS use Next.js App Router (not Pages Router)
- ALWAYS use React Server Components where appropriate
- ALWAYS use TailwindCSS for styling
- NEVER use inline styles
- ALWAYS implement proper error boundaries
- ALWAYS use React hooks correctly (no rules violations)

## Media Handling Rules
- ALWAYS request user permission for camera/microphone
- ALWAYS show visual indicator when recording
- ALWAYS handle getUserMedia errors gracefully
- NEVER persist media without explicit consent
- NEVER use MediaRecorder for audio — Gemini Live API REJECTS WebM/Opus entirely
- ALWAYS capture audio via AudioWorklet producing Int16 PCM at 16kHz (see AUDIO_PIPELINE.md)
- ALWAYS send audio as binary WebSocket frames (Int16Array.buffer), NOT JSON
- ALWAYS use AudioContext sampleRate 16000 for capture, 24000 for playback
- ALWAYS place pcm-processor.js and pcm-playback-processor.js in frontend/public/worklets/ (addModule requires a URL)
- ALWAYS optimize frame capture rate (1 fps max for vision)
- ALWAYS validate media before sending

## Security Rules
- ALWAYS validate and sanitize user inputs
- NEVER log sensitive data (API keys, tokens)
- ALWAYS use environment variables for secrets
- NEVER commit .env files to git
- ALWAYS implement rate limiting
- ALWAYS use HTTPS/WSS in production
- ALWAYS validate CORS origins

## Error Handling Rules
- ALWAYS catch specific exceptions first
- ALWAYS provide user-friendly error messages
- ALWAYS log errors with stack traces
- NEVER expose internal implementation details
- ALWAYS implement retry logic for transient failures
- ALWAYS clean up resources in finally blocks
- ALWAYS return appropriate HTTP status codes

## Testing Rules
- ALWAYS write tests for critical paths
- ALWAYS use pytest for Python tests
- ALWAYS use pytest-asyncio for async tests
- ALWAYS mock external API calls in tests
- NEVER skip tests without good reason
- ALWAYS test error conditions
- ALWAYS verify on Windows before marking complete

## Code Quality Rules
- ALWAYS follow PEP 8 for Python code
- ALWAYS use meaningful variable names
- ALWAYS add docstrings to functions/classes
- NEVER leave commented-out code
- ALWAYS remove debug print statements
- ALWAYS keep functions small and focused
- ALWAYS use early returns to reduce nesting

## Git Rules
- ALWAYS write clear commit messages
- ALWAYS commit working code only
- NEVER commit secrets or credentials
- ALWAYS use .gitignore properly
- ALWAYS create feature branches
- ALWAYS test before pushing

## Performance Rules
- ALWAYS use connection pooling for external APIs
- ALWAYS implement caching where appropriate
- NEVER perform heavy computation in request handlers
- ALWAYS use async for I/O-bound operations
- ALWAYS optimize database queries
- ALWAYS monitor memory usage
- ALWAYS profile before optimizing

## Documentation Rules
- ALWAYS update README when adding features
- ALWAYS document API endpoints
- ALWAYS add inline comments for complex logic
- NEVER assume code is self-documenting
- ALWAYS update architecture docs when changing structure
- ALWAYS document environment variables

## Deployment Rules
- ALWAYS use Docker for containerization
- ALWAYS test containers locally before deploying
- ALWAYS use multi-stage builds for smaller images
- ALWAYS set proper resource limits
- ALWAYS implement health checks
- ALWAYS use secrets management (not env vars in production)

## Phase Execution Rules
- ALWAYS complete current phase before starting next
- ALWAYS verify phase completion criteria
- NEVER skip verification steps
- ALWAYS test on Windows after each phase
- ALWAYS document any deviations from plan
- ALWAYS ask for clarification if requirements unclear

## Critical Rules (NEVER VIOLATE)
1. NEVER use bash/sh commands - ALWAYS use PowerShell
2. NEVER mock Gemini API - ALWAYS use real SDK (google-genai, NOT google-generativeai)
3. NEVER skip error handling - ALWAYS handle exceptions
4. NEVER block async functions - ALWAYS use await
5. NEVER commit secrets - ALWAYS use environment variables
6. NEVER skip testing - ALWAYS verify functionality
7. NEVER proceed if phase verification fails
8. NEVER ignore Windows compatibility issues
9. NEVER use MediaRecorder for audio - ALWAYS use AudioWorklet + Int16 PCM
10. NEVER deploy frontend to Vercel - ALWAYS use Firebase Hosting
11. NEVER read root-level AGENT_EXECUTION_PLAN.md or MASTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT.txt as authoritative — they are SUPERSEDED. The authoritative planning docs are in .planning/codebase/. See OPENCODE.md.

## When Stuck
- Read the error message carefully
- Check Windows-specific issues first
- Verify environment variables are set
- Check file paths use correct separators
- Verify Python venv is activated
- Check PowerShell execution policy if script fails
- Consult .planning/codebase/ARCHITECTURE.md and .planning/codebase/API_SCHEMAS.md (NOT root-level ARCHITECTURE.md or API_CONTRACTS.md)
- Ask for human guidance if truly blocked

## Master Orchestration File
READ OPENCODE.md IN THE PROJECT ROOT BEFORE DOING ANYTHING ELSE.
OPENCODE.md contains the complete skill install sequence, phase-by-phase reading order, file creation map, and authority matrix for all planning documents.
